'''Chennai Esports Global Championship''' is an esports championship series, organized by Skyesports.

For its first edition, it is held across [[Battlegrounds Mobile India|BGMI]] and [[counterstrike:Chennai_Esports_Global_Championship/2025|Counter-Strike 2]] titles with a total prizepool of ₹1,00,00,000 {{Abbr/INR}}.

==About==
===Format===
* '''Luna Open Qualifier:''''' October 21st - 22nd, 2025
** {{Bgcolortext|up|Top 1 team}} advance to ''Semi-Finals''.
* '''Closed Qualifier:''''' October 23rd - 24th, 2025
** {{Bgcolortext|up|Top 3 teams}} advance to ''Semi-Finals''.
<div style="margin-top:1em"></div>
* '''Semi-Finals:''''' November 4th - 7th, 2025
** 24 teams:
*** {{Bgcolortext|stayup|20 teams}} directly invited.
*** {{Bgcolortext|stayup|3 teams}} from Closed Qualifiers.
*** {{Bgcolortext|stayup|1 team}} from Luna Open Qualifier (Female team).
** Each team plays 16 matches.
** {{Bgcolortext|up|Top 8 teams}} advance to ''Grand Finals''.
** {{Bgcolortext|stay|Remaining teams}} advance to ''Last Chance Qualifier''.
<div style="margin-top:10px"></div>
* '''Last Chance Qualifier:''''' November 8th - 11th, 2025
** 16 teams.
** 24 matches.
** {{Bgcolortext|up|Top 8 teams}} advance to ''Grand Finals''.
** {{Bgcolortext|down|Remaining teams}} are ''eliminated''.
<div style="margin-top:12px"></div>
* '''Grand Finals:''''' November 14th - 16th, 2025
** 16 teams:
*** {{Bgcolortext|stayup|8 teams}} from Semi-Finals
*** {{Bgcolortext|stayup|8 teams}} from Last Chance Qualifier
** 18 matches (6 each day).
** '''Smash Rule''' is applied. {{SmashRule|matchpoint=Top 1's points after Match #12 + 10|maxmatch=6|margin-left=2em}}

